gland as a learned form in the 18th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Mathilda","meanings":["Latinized form of a Germanic personal name derived from <i>maht</i>, <i>meht</i> ‘might’ + <i>hild</i> ‘battle’. This was the name of an early German queen (  895–968 ), wife of  Henry  the Fowler, who was noted for her piety and generosity. It was also the name of the wife of  William  the Conqueror and of the daughter of  Henry I  of England (  see  Maud  ). The name was introduced into England by the Normans, and this Latinized form is the one that normally occurs in medieval records, while the vernacular form <i>Maud</i> was the one in everyday use. <i>Matilda</i> was revived in England as a learned form in the 18th century."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Abbess Matilda Of Barking was born in 1119, in Oxford, Oxfordshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Hugh Gobion I about 1145, in Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1175, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 56."},"et":{"1119–1175":"1119–1175","1115–1167":"1115–1167","1146–1182":"1146–1182","1115":"1115","Abt 1145":"umbes 1145","1146":"1146","1167":"1167","1175":"1175","about 1167":"umbes 1167","about 1146":"umbes 1146","1182":"1182","1119":"1119","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Northamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, England","Northhamptonshire, England":"Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Horton, Northamptonshire, England":"Horton, Northamptonshire, England"},"fi":{"1119–1175":"1119–1175","1115–1167":"1115–1167","1146–1182":"1146–1182","1115":"1115","Abt 1145":"noin 1145","1146":"1146","1167":"1167","1175":"1175","about 1167":"noin 1167","about 1146":"noin 1146","1182":"1182","1119":"1119","Oxford, Oxfordshire, England":"Oxford, Oxfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Northamptonshire, England":"Northam